<section class = "main-section" id = "Saber">
<header>Saber</header>
<p>Heroes known for using a type of sword in their legends or documentaries.</p>
<p>Considered the strongest class</p>
<li>Artoria
</section>
<section class = "main-section" id = "Archer">
<header>Archer</header>
<p>Heroes known for using a ranged weapon in their legends or documentaries.</p>
<p>Has a lot of sword-wielders too for some reason.</p>
<li>Gilgamesh
</section>
<section class = "main-section" id = "Lancer">
<header>Lancer</header>
<p>Heroes known for using spear, lances, or other polearms in their legends</p>
<p>A really strong class</p>
<li>Karna
</section>
<section class = "main-section" id = "Caster">
<header>Caster</header>
<p>Heroes known for using magic, staves, and rituals in their lore</p>
<p><code>Considered</code> one of the weakest combat classes</p>
<li>Tamamo no Mae
</section>
<section class = "main-section" id = "Rider">
<header>Rider</header>
<p>Heroes known for riding as part of their legends. </p>
<p><code>Very strange</code> to have a class based off a <code>verb</code>, I know, but considering some servants in this class have divine steeds, it's <code>cool</code></p>
<li>Iskandar
</section>
<section class = "main-section" id = "Assassin">
<header>Assassin</header>
<p>"Heroes" known for using stealth tactics to kill in their legends</p>
<p>One of the <code>edgier</code> classes</p>
<li>First/King Hassan
</section>
<section class = "main-section" id = "Berserker">
<header>Berserker</header>
<p>Heroes known for madness, brutality, and/or rage.</p>
<p>Some servants in other classes have a berserker version, which points to parts of their lore and/or backstory</p>
<li>Heracles
</section>
